text: Although closed, I wanted to say that the head chef, Generoso Bahena, had the right idea. He faithfully prepared the mole Guerrero style. Although you could get Guerrero-style food elsewhere for less, I give him props for putting out cusine on the map.  For now, I am looking forward to trying Restaurant y Pozoleria San Juan and Lo Mejor de Guerrero. I will give a Yelp once ive tried them.

Love, Love, Love this restaurant.  It is absolutely the best authentic Mexican food I have ever had.  It is definitely on the fancier side of dining, but great for a special occasion or go for a great lunch and a margherita.  The other great thing is that they have over 100 different kinds of Tequila, and even if you are not a fan, you will definitely appreciate it...

One of the most upscale mexican restaraunts i have ever seen.  The food is extremely well done, try one of their famous mole sauces.  Margaritas are very good, and they have a bunch of desserts.  Order the "chicago fire" its a tableside coffe drink , and it is quite a show, lots of flaming booze involved.
The food is so good here!  Try the flaming coffee, its definitely a big production and tastes good too!  $$$
